1 A bill to be entitled
2 An act relating to the rights of crime victims;
3 amending s. 960.001, F.S.; providing that a victim may
4 refuse to communicate with the defendant's attorney;
5 providing that a victim may require that the
6 prosecutor be notified of and present for
7 communications with the defendant's attorney; amending
8 s. 960.0021, F.S.; revising an announcement by which a
9 court may advise a crime victim of his or her rights;
10 providing an effective date.
11
12 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Florida:
13
14 Section 1. Subsections (7), (8), and (9) of section
15 960.001, Florida Statutes, are renumbered as subsections (8),
16 (9), and (10), respectively, and a new subsection (7) is added
17 to that section to read:
18 960.001 Guidelines for fair treatment of victims and
19 witnesses in the criminal justice and juvenile justice systems.—
20 (7) A victim may:
21 (a) Refuse to communicate with the defendant's attorney.
22 (b) Require that the prosecutor be notified of and present
23 for any and all communications between the defendant's attorney
24 and the victim.
