26 960.0021, Florida Statutes, is amended to read:
27 960.0021 Legislative intent; advisement to victims.—
28 (2) The courts may fulfill their obligation to advise
29 crime victims by doing one of the following:
30 (a) Making the following announcement at any arraignment,
31 sentencing, or case-management proceeding:
32
33 "If you are the victim of a crime with a case pending before
34 this court, you are advised that you have the right, upon
35 request:
36 1. To be informed.
37 2. To be present.
38 3. To be heard at all stages of criminal proceedings.
39 4. To receive advance notification, when possible, of
40 judicial proceedings and notification of scheduling changes,
41 pursuant to section 960.001, Florida Statutes.
42 5. To seek crimes compensation and restitution.
43 6. To consult with the state attorney's office in certain
44 felony cases regarding the disposition of the case.
45 7. To make an oral or written victim impact statement at
46 the time of sentencing of a defendant.
47 8. To refuse to communicate with the defendant's attorney.
48 9. To have the prosecutor notified of and present for any
49 and all communications with the defendant's attorney.
